								<p>Boba tea was first created in Taiwan in the 1980s. The original version consisted of black tea, milk, sugar, and tapioca pearls. It quickly became popular for its unique texture and refreshing taste. Over the years, boba tea has evolved, with countless variations now available, catering to different tastes and preferences.</p>
