									<p>Boba tea is typically served cold, although hot versions are also available. It's enjoyed with a wide straw that allows the tapioca pearls to be sipped along with the tea. The experience of chewing the boba while drinking the tea is part of what makes this beverage so unique and enjoyable.</p>

								</blockquote>

